	.ch-g3-4
		h1 Layer
		p.container
			| The Layer component is a member of 
			a(href='/api/#{latest.version}/symbols/ch.Floats.html') Floats
			|  familiy. Gives rich information about an UI element on the screen.
		a(id='demo')
		h2 Demo
		p.container
			| Hold the mouse over the ninjas for a few seconds:
		p.actions
			img.ninjas(src='/src/assets/ninjas.jpg')
		.snippet
			p Snippet
			div
				pre.code
					| <span id="example">Move cursor over me!!</span>
		p.container
			| As any 
			a(href='/api/#{latest.version}/symbols/ch.Floats.html') Floats
			|  children, the Layer has a few uses cases you can use to modifiy and manipulate
			| its content, its size and positioning. 
		p.container	
			| This is the way to create a new Layer:
		pre.code
			| var foo = $("#example").layer("<p>Rich content.</p>"); // Create a layer component
		a(id='show-and-hide')
		h2 Show and hide
		p.container
			| All 
			a(href='/api/#{latest.version}/symbols/ch.Floats.html') Floats
			|  exposes some public methods called 
			code show()
			|  and 
			code hide()
			| , both allow you to manage the layer's behavior programmatically. Something like this:
		pre.code
			| foo.show(); // Shows the layer
		p.container
			| Or
			code hide()
			|  the Layer, like this:
		pre.code
			| foo.hide(); // Hides the layer
		p.container
			| Read more about 
			a(href='/api/#{latest.version}/symbols/ch.Floats.html') Floats
			| .

		a(id='get-and-set-content')
		h2 Get and set content
		p.container
			| All 
			a(href='/api/#{latest.version}/symbols/ch.Floats.html') Floats
			|  exposes a public method called 
			code content()
			| , it works as a getter and a setter at the same time. To 
			em get 
			| the content of this component simply use the method without arguments, like this:
		pre.code
			| var content = foo.content(); // Get its content
		p.container
			| To 
			em set 
			| content add an argument to the method  
			code content()
			| , admits static content, DOM content or AJAX content. See an example:
		pre.code
			| foo.content("New content!"); // Set its content
		p.container
			| Read more about 
			a(href='/api/#{latest.version}/symbols/ch.Object.html#.content') Content
			| .
			
		a(id='changing-size')
		h2 Changing size
		p.container
			| For change the width property to the layer's container
			| there is a method called 
			code width()
			| , also works as a getter and a setter at the same time. To 
			em get 
			| the property simply use the method without arguments, like this:
		pre.code
			| var width = foo.width(); // Get its width
		p.container
			| To set the property add an argument to the method  
			code width()
			| , admits 
			em Numbers
			|  (33) or 
			em String
			|  ('33px') as a CSS property. See an example:
		pre.code
			| foo.width(300); // Set its width
		p.container
			| Exactly the same thing with the method 
			code heigth()
			| , admits 
			em Numbers
			|  (22) or 
			em String
			| ('22px') as a CSS property. Get example:
		pre.code
			| foo.height(); // Get its height
		p.container
			| Set 
			code height()
			|  examples:
		pre.code
			| foo.height(300); // Set its height
		p.container
			| Read more about 
			a(href='/api/#{latest.version}/symbols/ch.Floats.html#.size') Sizing
			| .
			
		a(id='positioning')
		h2 Positioning
		p.container
			| Chico has an great utility to position things on screen, is called 
			a(href='/api/#{latest.version}/symbols/ch.Positioner.html') Positioner
			| . All 
			a(href='/api/#{latest.version}/symbols/ch.Floats.html') Floats
			|  has a 
			code position()
			|  method related to the 
			a(href='/api/#{latest.version}/symbols/ch.Positioner.html') Positioner
			|  , you can use it to redefine 
			| layer's positioning. See an example:			
		pre.code
			| foo.position({ 
			|   offset: "0 10",
			|   points: "lt lb"
			| });
		p.container
			| As you can see, we pass a configuration object to the 
			code position()
			|  method with some properties. The 
			code offset
			|  property let you define a specific pixel values for X and Y axis indentation.
			| The 
			code points
			|  property defines the position relation between the element and its context.
			| In this case, the value 
			code "lt lb"
			|  literally says: 
			cite 
				| The element will be positioned by joining its left-bottom point with its 
				| context by its left-top point. 
		p.container
			| Read more about 
			a(href='/api/#{latest.version}/symbols/ch.Positioner.html') Positioner
			| .

